  "text": "• C and subsequently used for further analysis. For high pressure liquid chromatography (HPLC) separation experiments (see below), the synthesis was scaled up 4-fold to yield a final reaction volume of 200 l. For fluorescence spectroscopy, the 50 l samples were diluted with 450 l of distilled water before measurement on a Horiba Jobin Yvon, Fluoromax-4 fluorimeter in a 10 mm disposable cuvette (5 nm slit for excitation and 10 nm for emission). For absorbance and circular dichroism spectroscopy (see below), the dilution was only by a factor 4 to yield a final volume of 200 l. For fluorescence spectroscopy of animal samples, the 50 l samples were diluted with 100 l of distilled water before measurement on a CLARIOstar microplate reader (BMG LABTECH, Ortenberg, Germany). All spectroscopic measurements were performed at room temperature [CITATION_1] • C).",
